  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cameroon Cholera Response - SW and Littoral Regions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Prevention and control of the disease&amp;#58; Advocacy and dialogue sessions; Training of community influencers, youths and women leaders to reinforce awareness of Cholera and preventive measures for them to champion sensitization activities; The CHW will raise awareness of cholera prevention measures in the home and identify potential cases in the communities; Purchase and distribution of WASH kits; Support the health District in place with PPE materials

Case management&amp;#58; Integrated community case management (ICCM)

Building community resilience and access to portable drinking water and sanitation&amp;#58; Carry out participatory hygiene and sanitation transformation in communities.
Cross cutting activities&amp;#58; Monitoring and supervision; Post Distribution Monitoring</narrative>
  </description>
